abstract: Seven books present a nuanced view of this giant’s legacy in modern American civil rights.
snippet: Seven books present a nuanced view of this giant’s legacy in modern American civil rights.
lead_paragraph: As is often the case with those who die young, Martin Luther King Jr. has become more symbol than man: pacifist, beacon of nonviolent racial reform. But over the last 50 years since his assassination, that view has been complicated. His “I Have a Dream” speech, taught in schools and exalted for its vision of a racial utopia, has been re-examined, showing how King’s views evolved in his final years, recognizing how much work remained to be done to achieve true equality. These books paint a complete picture of King, including biographies, novels and King’s final written work.

headline.main: Remembering Martin Luther King Jr.
